Text.Value: From where do you hail?
What did you mean to accomplish in the grove?
Leave.
In shadow... a gift from Cloakwood...
Stole the idol... needed for ritual... choice and consequence...

RuleGroup.RuleString: BARD or DRUID or WARLOCK or WIZARD

Text.Value: This rite is powerful magic. How did you come by it?
This magic is ordered. Powerful. Someone gave it to you. Who?
Complete the Rite of Thorns... safe from the coming storm...
Halsin... gave to Rath...
The power to... protect my people... sanctuary...
Why did you take the tiefling girl?

EditorData.logicalname: Know Arabella was there (heard from parents or entered lair)

Text.Value: Why did you ally with the Shadow Druids?
What happened to you? How did you come to die?
Born to the circle... belonged to the circle...
Emerald Enclave... rightful First Druid...
*The corpse does not stir. It will answer no more questions.*
*The corpse regards you lifelessly.*
Who were you in life?
Punished for... protecting the grove...
*The spell's power wanes. You can ask no more questions.*
A rune is missing in the enclave library. Where can I find it?
*The corpse seems willing to speak - but not to its killer.*

Synopsis: Speak with dead with Kagha. Halting delivery in the way of other SWD dialogues.
